  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Currently, API registration is in done in the [`registered` package](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/api/registered/registered.go) and the `install` package in each API, e.g., [the `install` package for group \"\"](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/api/install/install.go). The `registered` package keeps a hard-coded list of valid GroupVersions and a hard-coded list of GroupVersions that are enabled by default. This is against our goal of separating API machinery from the API.\n\nWe plan to remove the `init()` in package `registered` and do all the API initialization in each `install` package. To do so, we conceptually split the API initialization into 2 steps: \nThe first step is registration, instead of a hard-coded list, each install package adds their group/versions to the `registered.validGroupVersions` list;\nThe second step is installation, each `install` package calls a function provided by the `registered` package to learn which group/version the user wants to install, as expressed in KUBE_API_VERSIONS, and then install them. If the environment variable is not set, then all registered group/version will be installed.\n\nThe `install` package should export the installation function so that an API can be installed after initialization. [edit] The installation function installs the API without checking `KUBE_API_VERSIONS`. I think @nikhiljindal needs this feature for his apiserver library.\n\ncc @nikhiljindal @deads2k \n",
